=== Noun ===
'''[[past]] [[participle]]'''

#{{grammar}}: a [[participle]] indicating a completed action or state, and functioning as an [[adjective]]. When combined with the [[verb]] ''to [[be]]'', a past participle forms the [[perfect tense]]s of a verb. In a [[regular verb]], the past participle ends in -''ed'' and has the same spelling as the [[past tense]] of the verb. Sometimes the last consonant needs to be doubled. Sometimes the end vowels change: y -> ied.

==== Examples ====
*to [[love]], loved, '''loved'''
*to [[construct]], constructed, '''constructed'''
*to [[justify]], justified, '''justified'''
*to [[listen]], listened, '''listened'''
*to [[beg]], begged, '''begged'''

For the [[irregular verb]]s you may refer to the [[Wiktionary Appendix:Irregular verbs|list of irregular verbs]]

